Package com.energyxxer.commodore.types

Class Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.energyxxer.commodore.types.Type
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BiomeType, BlockType, BossbarReference, DifficultyType, DimensionType, EffectType, EnchantmentType, EntityType, FluidType, FunctionReference, GamemodeType, GameruleType, GenericType, ItemSlot, ItemType, ParticleType, StructureType, Tag, TeamReference
    public abstract class Type
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines a type of a Minecraft object of a certain category.
    Such categories are, by default, blocks, items, fluids, entities, biomes, difficulties, dimensions, status effects, enchantments, gamemodes, gamerules, item slots, particles, structures, functions and bossbars.
    These types can be provided either via definition packs or by creating them via the TypeDictionary.create(java.lang.String) method of the corresponding category in the TypeManager of the corresponding Namespace of the CommandModule. Definition packs can also define their own categories.
    See Also:
    DefinitionPack, TypeDictionary, TypeManager, Namespace, CommandModule, GenericType

      • useNamespace

        public boolean useNamespace()
        Describes whether or not this type is namespace-sensitive, and whether it should print the namespace when used in a command. If this returns true, the namespace field should not be null.
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is a sensitive part of its declaration, false if it's not.

      • isStandalone

        public abstract boolean isStandalone()
        Describes whether or not this type alone is enough to set an instance of itself. For instance, if this type object refers to a block tag, this type is not standalone, as it is not enough to be able to set a block of this type. In short, this dictates whether or not this type is a standalone definition, or if it describes multiple types at once.
        Returns:
        true if this type can be set and tested, false if this type can only be tested.
